      "content": "I hear the profound sense of loss and disconnection you're describing. It sounds like the creative spark that once fueled your sense of self has faded, leaving you feeling like a hollow vessel. That feeling of being a \"ghost\" in your own body, where the connection to beauty and creation is gone, can be incredibly isolating and overwhelming.\n\nIt's a heavy realization to come to, especially when the thing that made you feel real seems to have vanished forever. Sometimes, when the creative outlet that defined us disappears, it can feel like the whole person disappears with it.\n\nWould you be willing to explore what might be happening beneath the surface of this emptiness? Are there other parts of you that you haven't been able to reach, or perhaps other ways of connecting with the world that haven't been explored yet?",
      "source": "target",
